Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.47,0:00:15.08,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to shine on you,\Nand always like that dazzling sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.38,0:00:18.75,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will defend you\Nfrom all the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.85,0:00:24.75,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.76,0:00:39.54,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If only our hearts could connect,\NI could get you to believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.64,0:00:46.31,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you can't\Nsee it now, don't lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.48,0:00:54.25,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your kindness won't be in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.08,0:01:01.66,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be carried aloft by the wind\Nto somewhere that isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.06,0:01:08.77,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll cross the sea and cross time,\Nand I know you'll blossom one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.93,0:01:15.41,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever the day,\NI'll be there for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.84,0:01:22.05,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hope I can watch over you\Nlike the sun for all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.05,0:01:32.02,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.86,0:02:11.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that you, Balsa?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.23,0:02:15.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You sure took your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.20,0:02:19.37,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We were worried that you'd been\Ncaptured by those people from the palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.44,0:02:20.37,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Chagum?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.37,0:02:21.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.54,0:02:30.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard the particulars\Nof what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.71,0:02:33.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We have no choice but to head\Nstraight for Toumi village, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.52,0:02:34.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.35,0:02:35.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.62,0:02:37.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.06,0:02:43.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to go back to the palace and\Nfind out what happened to my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.69,0:02:47.73,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If it turns out that\Nhe truly is dead, then I...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.73,0:02:50.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No. I can't allow you\Nto go back to the palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.00,0:02:54.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll explain why later.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.84,0:02:58.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, the first thing we need\Nto do is to shake our pursuers!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.98,0:03:06.98,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 18\NThe Ancient Village
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.08,0:03:10.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How did the prince appear to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.59,0:03:13.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,His appearance\Nhad utterly changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.82,0:03:18.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To the extent that he would pass for\Nany child of the city at first glance...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.20,0:03:21.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He must have disguised\Nhimself to prevent...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.83,0:03:24.37,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...residents of the\Npalace from finding him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.97,0:03:26.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.87,0:03:31.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,One thing remained unchanged.\NHe seemed as lively and sound as ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.35,0:03:42.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I heard what happened\Nfrom Master Shuga.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.72,0:03:44.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did you have any luck?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.49,0:03:48.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, I searched all\Nover Ogi no Shimo.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.23,0:03:52.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I have been\Nof no use whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.00,0:03:57.63,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am simply thankful that we have\Nconfirmed that he is alive and well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.40,0:04:02.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is most important now is that\Nwe do not fail in our next attempt.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.24,0:04:03.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Zen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.11,0:04:04.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.61,0:04:09.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.68,0:04:13.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The goods that the errand runner\Ndelivered to the spear-wielder.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.42,0:04:15.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She was preparing\Nto set out on a journey?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.19,0:04:18.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But from what I saw...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.82,0:04:22.73,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the prince didn't seem to have\Nany clue until just a few hours before...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.73,0:04:25.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...that he was about\Nto go on the run again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.53,0:04:29.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It appears that the spear-wielder\Nwas planning to set out for somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.87,0:04:33.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...even before she\Nbumped into you, Master Shuga.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.40,0:04:36.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fortunately, the contents of this pack\Nwill allow us to deduce her destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.94,0:04:38.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.98,0:04:42.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Judging from these quantities, she was\Nplanning a three-day trip with the prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.11,0:04:44.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is not enough to cross\Nthe Misty Blue Mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.08,0:04:49.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,From this, we can deduce\Nthat they will either go south...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.32,0:04:52.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...on the Tonan highway or they'll enter\Nthe mountainous region to the east.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.19,0:04:54.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is no chance that they\Nwill go to Rota or Sangal?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.26,0:04:59.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to believe that they would\Nmake for the border carrying provisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.13,0:05:01.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There are any number\Nof inns along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.50,0:05:02.73,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.73,0:05:06.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I shall start by dispatching\Nrunners to the Tonan highway barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.90,0:05:09.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That will make it a simple\Nmatter to find the prince...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.61,0:05:11.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...on the single road\Nleading to the coast.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.14,0:05:13.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Which leaves the\Nmountains to the east.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.98,0:05:14.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.58,0:05:19.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now why would the\Nbodyguard travel east?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.72,0:05:23.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They aren't as high\Nas the Misty Blues...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.99,0:05:27.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but the area is largely unexplored\Nand covered with primeval forests.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.26,0:05:32.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't think of anything there besides\Na handful of Yakoo settlements.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.73,0:05:37.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! The Yakoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.40,0:05:42.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When I met the bodyguard, I was\Nperplexed by her words and actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.21,0:05:45.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She seemed to know\Neven more about...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.17,0:05:48.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the spirit within\NPrince Chagum than I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.68,0:05:51.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wondered how someone\Nfrom Kanbal could know so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.28,0:05:54.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She must have gained this\Nknowledge from the Yakoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.72,0:05:56.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.29,0:06:01.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That would also explain the\Nmud dolls we found on the valley floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.22,0:06:04.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...instead of the prince and her\Nup in the Misty Blue Mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.90,0:06:09.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is a Yakoo settlement called\NYashiro village beyond the terrace fields...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.40,0:06:11.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...where we first\Ncrossed swords with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.97,0:06:15.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So she had a Yakoo accomplice\Nin addition to the errand runner...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.97,0:06:19.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps, but a trip to Yashiro\Nwouldn't call for such preparations.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.91,0:06:23.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And even if they intended to travel to\Na settlement farther off in that direction...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.68,0:06:28.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I doubt they would travel to their initial\Ndestination now that we've located them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.92,0:06:31.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will keep that possibility\Nin mind, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.29,0:06:34.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will have them step up surveillance\Non the Sangal and Rota barriers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.73,0:06:39.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Shuga, perhaps it would be\Nwise to summon troops right away...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.96,0:06:44.63,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...to check every highway, as well as\Nsearch Kosenkyo from top to bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.63,0:06:47.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That would take far too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.47,0:06:49.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And one other thing, Mon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.84,0:06:56.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot help but think that the bodyguard\Nis thinking the same thing I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.55,0:07:04.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I believe that she needs to find a fresh\Nsource of information, just as I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.77,0:07:25.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.74,0:07:29.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let me carry you on my back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.18,0:07:33.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Go on, don't be shy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.58,0:07:35.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Walk on your own\Ntwo feet, Chagum.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.29,0:07:39.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right, Balsa. I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.76,0:07:44.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If he carries you, who's\Ngoing to carry his pack?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.89,0:07:46.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Torogai?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.33,0:07:47.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.80,0:07:51.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or is Tanda going to carry\Nboth you and his own pack?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.90,0:07:54.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, you don't\Nhave to be like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.27,0:07:57.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, I'll walk on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.01,0:08:04.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And while we're walking, tell me\Nabout the egg that's inside me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.31,0:08:09.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me what's more important\Nthan my brother dying!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.15,0:08:10.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's no time for that now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.79,0:08:20.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.23,0:08:23.93,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.91,0:08:35.75,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So Toya...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.01,0:08:40.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. If he hadn't\Nrisked his life like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.58,0:08:44.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I probably wouldn't be\Nstanding here right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.79,0:08:49.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Torogai is taking forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.59,0:08:53.63,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's been quite a while\Nsince she last went to Toumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.23,0:08:58.93,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's not it. This is just her way\Nof showing concern for Chagum.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.14,0:09:05.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Actually, I've been\Nto Toumi once myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.44,0:09:09.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't remember anything\Nabout how to get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.78,0:09:14.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was brought there by my uncle when\NI was even younger than Chagum.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.28,0:09:15.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.35,0:09:20.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My grandmother on my mother's\Nside came from Toumi village.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.39,0:09:24.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Initially, she left Toumi\Nto marry my grandfather...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.66,0:09:29.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but once my mother married into\Nthe family, they both retired to Toumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.73,0:09:31.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did I ever tell you about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.23,0:09:33.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No. Are they still alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.10,0:09:37.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure. Probably not.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.01,0:09:44.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How are you planning to tell Chagum?\NYou know, about the egg-eater...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.45,0:09:46.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know. It's a touchy subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.48,0:09:50.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, his brother died recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.65,0:09:53.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you should wait until he's had\Na chance to come to terms with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.32,0:09:56.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, we'll have to talk to\Nhim about it eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.06,0:09:58.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't something that\Nwe can keep from him forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.43,0:10:02.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He'll have to learn the truth\Nand gain strength from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.17,0:10:09.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So once we reach Toumi and find\Nsome way to fight it, I'll tell him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.71,0:10:14.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rejoice. I found the way through.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.95,0:10:19.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Also, I found us some food.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.35,0:10:27.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The vagrants who use this as a\Nshelter appear to have seen them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.26,0:10:30.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost certain\Nthat it was the prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.99,0:10:36.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Both that old woman and the\NYakoo man are likely her accomplices.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.60,0:10:42.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We just spotted a smoke\Nsignal from Zen and Yun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.61,0:10:47.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There doesn't appear to be any sign of\Nthe spear-wielder stopping at Tokal village.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.14,0:10:50.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Taga and Sune were\Ninvestigating other settlements...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.15,0:10:51.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and they sent the same signal.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.95,0:10:55.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In which case,\Nall that's left is Toumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.32,0:10:58.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard that Toumi\Nis one of the few villages...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.42,0:11:01.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...where the ancient Yakoo\Nways have been preserved.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.09,0:11:03.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right, we will go on ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.09,0:11:04.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a moment, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.46,0:11:09.73,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The terrain between here and Toumi\Nis difficult by horse, much less on foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.97,0:11:12.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Jin and I will go on ahead first.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.80,0:11:14.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I believe the safest\Ncourse of action...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.67,0:11:17.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...is for you to rendezvous with\Nthe others and follow our lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.84,0:11:19.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we can't go by horse?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.41,0:11:24.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. I will join you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.48,0:11:27.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, even if you\Ncatch sight of the prince...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.02,0:11:30.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...please do not take\Nany action until I arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.45,0:11:35.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is something that\NI want to ask them in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.96,0:11:40.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.\NWe shall do as you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.57,0:11:52.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Teacher, are you sure\Nthis is a shortcut?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.08,0:11:55.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This should save us half a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.25,0:11:57.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Still not ripe, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.06,0:12:16.07,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Moribito Guardian of the Spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.48,0:13:09.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Weather in the mountains\Nsure changes quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.52,0:13:11.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Which means this will\Nlet up soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.79,0:13:21.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There are no traces of them,\Nbut I find that all the more suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.50,0:13:23.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I concur.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.20,0:13:26.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But there are no\Nclues to follow, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.20,0:13:33.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we'll soon have our\Nfirst proper meal in two days.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.08,0:13:37.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're hungry too,\Naren't you, Chagum?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.19,0:13:49.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A monkey?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.43,0:13:50.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.84,0:14:07.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you from around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.12,0:14:18.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.79,0:14:23.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you related to Kunda?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.33,0:14:32.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see now. You must\Nknow my grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.84,0:14:38.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Kunda was always\Nvery good to my family...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.01,0:14:42.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...so I could tell right away that\Nyou were related to him, Tanda.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.21,0:14:47.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. You must look\Nlike your grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.75,0:14:50.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,By the way,\Nwould that happen to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.85,0:14:55.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this? This is mashira liquor\Nthat I gathered in the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.02,0:14:56.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.29,0:14:57.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.52,0:15:24.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is called a "road's end rope."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.42,0:15:28.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it's a charm where you rattle\Nthe nahji bird bones strung on it...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.49,0:15:31.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...to prevent evil\Nspirits from entering.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.23,0:15:35.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've seen these in\NYogo villages from time to time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.50,0:15:40.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's just the Yogo people\Nimitating Yakoo traditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.44,0:15:45.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The proper way to do it is to string it\Nup across the entrance to a village.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.15,0:15:54.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go. It looks like Toumi\Nvillage is just across that hill.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.41,0:16:26.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's as if the Yakoo way of life before\Nthe Yogoans arrived is preserved here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.79,0:16:39.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose they don't often\Nsee people like Chagum and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.13,0:16:40.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.53,0:16:43.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So good of you to come!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.63,0:16:45.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Soya, the village headman.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.67,0:16:49.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's been many a year since we\Nlast had outsiders visit our village.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.37,0:16:54.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you him? The one they\Nsay is Kunda's grandson?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.84,0:16:56.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're his spitting image, all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.75,0:17:04.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I regret to tell you that Kunda\Npassed away two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.19,0:17:10.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, we didn't come\Nhere to visit my grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.16,0:17:13.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We hope to gain insight from\Nyour knowledge of the old ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.90,0:17:17.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We have a lot of questions for\Nyou about the Nyunga Ro Chaga.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.77,0:17:24.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Standing out here talking\Nwon't do any good.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.84,0:17:26.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,First, please come to my home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.88,0:17:28.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll talk afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.75,0:17:43.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why in the world did you come all this\Nway to ask about some old legend?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.03,0:17:47.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we're in a bit of\Na complicated situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.80,0:17:51.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If possible, we'd like to ask your\Nstoryteller detailed questions about...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.87,0:17:56.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the changing of the Nyunga Ro Im\Nthat happened a hundred years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.57,0:18:02.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is it almost time again for the\Nchanging of the protector of the waters?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.34,0:18:03.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, just about.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.51,0:18:05.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then, in a sense, you're in luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.45,0:18:09.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard that my father's\Nolder brother, who died young...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.28,0:18:11.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...was a Nyunga Ro Chaga.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.29,0:18:14.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.22,0:18:20.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but my grandmother was so full\Nof grief whenever she spoke of him...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.60,0:18:23.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...that I don't remember\Nmuch in the way of details.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.87,0:18:28.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, my mother was\Nthe village's last storyteller.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.10,0:18:33.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She died last year, so there\Nis hardly anyone left in the village...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.34,0:18:37.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...who can tell you much about\Nthe Nyunga Ro Chaga now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.58,0:18:41.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you abandon\Nyour storyteller traditions?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.72,0:18:48.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I'm sure you're aware, the training\Nto become a storyteller is most harsh.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.16,0:18:50.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,From an early age,\Nyou are forced to learn...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.69,0:18:54.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...thousands of oral traditions\Nfrom sunup to sundown.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.46,0:18:58.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is cruel to force all\Nthat on any one person.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.73,0:19:05.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't care much for such practices,\Nso I decided not to appoint a successor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.54,0:19:10.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And besides, we now have the\Nofficial history of Shin Yogo to consult.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.91,0:19:15.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shameful! So this place is no\Ndifferent from the palace after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.69,0:19:22.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.36,0:19:28.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I heard stories about the Nyunga\NRo Chaga from my grandmother...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.16,0:19:30.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...so I think I can tell\Nyou a few of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.20,0:19:36.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, you used to visit my\Nmother carrying yamabime, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.11,0:19:38.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anything you can tell us\Nwould be appreciated.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.21,0:19:42.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Can you tell us what you\Nheard from your grandmother?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.98,0:19:44.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.58,0:19:50.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,According to my grandmother...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.42,0:19:54.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...in the body of my great-grandfather's\Nolder brother, the one who died young...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.59,0:19:58.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the egg of Nyunga Ro Im\Nsuddenly appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.06,0:20:03.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nyunga Ro Im is a spirit who lives\Ndeep underwater in Nayug's seas...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.57,0:20:06.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and is shaped\Nlike a giant shellfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.14,0:20:12.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The life force from its mouth becomes\Nclouds in Sagu and creates rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.31,0:20:17.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But once every hundred years,\NNyunga Ro Im lays an egg and dies.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.21,0:20:23.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When that happens,\Nthe clouds vanish from the skies...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.12,0:20:25.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and we experience\Na period of dry weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.02,0:20:29.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She said we have cared for the\Nguardian of the spirit since ancient times...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.66,0:20:33.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...so that the egg of the\Nnext spirit would hatch safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.10,0:20:37.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But that is usually only\Nuntil the egg matures.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.23,0:20:42.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When the time comes for\NNyunga Ro Im's egg to hatch...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.97,0:20:47.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the guardian travels alone to the\Nland of feasting, never to be seen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.18,0:20:53.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Overcome with grief,\Nmy great-grandmother's mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.92,0:20:58.75,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...begged the people of the village\Nto help protect her son as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.75,0:21:01.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...as he had become\Na guardian of the spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.66,0:21:05.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You know, I remember\Nhearing about that myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.10,0:21:19.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Shuga, it's a\Nsignal from the commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.84,0:21:23.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like there is\Na shortcut in that direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.41,0:21:24.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.35,0:21:27.38,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And beyond it lies Toumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.38,0:21:31.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, what did the villagers do\Nwith the Nyunga Ro Chaga?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.39,0:21:34.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When the spring day\Nof equality drew near...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.06,0:21:38.63,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the Nyunga Ro Chaga left the village\Nlike a bird beginning its migration.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.83,0:21:42.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The adult villagers\Nfollowed him on his long journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.06,0:21:47.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At long last, they reached a large spring\Nat the headwaters of the Aoyumi River...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.84,0:21:49.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...where the shigu salua\Nbloomed everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.61,0:21:56.38,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There, the guardian of the spirit\Nprepared to return the egg to Nayug.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.38,0:22:00.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But Rarunga had also come\Nto this spring from Nayug.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.25,0:22:05.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Like an egg-eating snake striking its prey,\NRarunga attacked the Nyunga Ro Chaga.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.09,0:22:08.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And before the eyes\Nof the watching adults...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.42,0:22:12.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...using enormous claws that could\Nbe neither seen nor felt by humans...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.89,0:22:16.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...it ripped the\NNyunga Ro Chaga in two.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.05,0:22:36.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Am I... Am I going to die\Nlike that too, Balsa?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.56,0:22:44.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Die like what?\NWho in the world is this child?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.40,0:22:53.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The fact is, this boy is\Nthe current Nyunga Ro Chaga.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.72,0:23:13.05,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I sat huddled and alone, holding\Nback the tears on those nights...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.05,0:23:20.20,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When it felt like I was about\Nto succumb to my doubts...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.20,0:23:25.47,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...there you were,\Nat my side before I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.47,0:23:32.81,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was none other than you\Nwho was there for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.81,0:23:47.09,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I keep wishing, "I want to be strong."\NI stumble and hurt myself again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.09,0:23:56.46,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But because I have you to believe in,\NI can get back to my feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.46,0:24:03.24,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I simply want to tell\Nmy dear one, "Thank you. "
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.24,0:24:08.38,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At the top of my lungs,\Nagain and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.38,0:24:16.75,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I call out to my precious loved one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.75,0:24:20.96,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is my voice reaching you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.96,0:24:29.20,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In this world that always changes,\Nhuman warmth never does.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.20,0:24:39.51,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certain I sensed the presence\Nof the one that I hold dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.01,0:24:45.91,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next Time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.78,0:24:47.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is when they are beaten down by\Nfate that people reveal their true selves.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.58,0:24:50.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They become distressed, angry,\Nand then they cross paths.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.79,0:24:53.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "Escape."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.02,0:24:57.03,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 19\NEscape
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.12,0:24:56.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa wields her weapon\Nfilled with determination.
